00:00:47,379 --> 00:00:48,571
<i>Roger that.</i>

3
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,415
<i>Inspired by
the late President Kennedy...</i>

4
00:00:51,484 --> 00:00:56,422
<i>in only seven years, America has risen
to the challenge of what he called:</i>

5
00:00:56,790 --> 00:01:00,283
<i>"The most hazardous and dangerous
and greatest adventure..."</i>

6
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:02,861
<i>"on which man has ever embarked."</i>

7
00:01:03,129 --> 00:01:07,533
<i>After trailing the Russians for years
with our manned space program...</i>

8
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,536
<i>and after that sudden and horrible fire...</i>

9
00:01:10,603 --> 00:01:13,004
<i>on the launch pad during a routine test...</i>

10
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:15,872
<i>that killed
American astronauts Gus Grissom...</i>

11
00:01:15,942 --> 00:01:18,275
<i>Ed White and Roger Chaffee...</i>

12
00:01:18,378 --> 00:01:22,007
<i>there were serious doubts that
we could beat the Russians to the moon.</i>

13
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:26,109
<i>But tonight, a mere 18 months
after the tragedy of</i> Apollo 1...

14
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:30,247
<i>the entire world watched in awe
as Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin...</i>

15
00:01:30,357 --> 00:01:31,915
<i>landed on the moon.</i>

16
00:01:32,025 --> 00:01:34,551
<i>The big news came just a moment ago.</i>

17
00:01:34,627 --> 00:01:37,597
<i>Mission Control gave
the spacecraft permission...</i>

18
00:01:37,697 --> 00:01:40,530
<i>to go for the extravehicular activity...</i>

19
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,534
<i>that is, for the walk on the moon...</i>

20
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:47,267
<i>far earlier than anticipated,
9:00 p.m. Eastern Daylight Time...</i>

21
00:01:47,474 --> 00:01:51,376
The important thing when you penetrate
the lunar module is your attitude...

22
00:01:51,544 --> 00:01:52,910
and relative speed.

23
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:56,538
Let's say this is me here
in the command module and this is you...

24
00:01:56,616 --> 00:01:58,209
- All right.
- ...in the LEM.

25
